{{Infobox video game | title = MotionSports | image = MotionSports Coverart.png | caption = | developer = [[Ubisoft Milan]] | publisher = [[Ubisoft]] | series = [[Kinect]] | released = {{vgrelease|NA|November 4, 2010|EU|November 10, 2010|AUS|November 18, 2010}} | genre = [[Sports video game|Sports]] | modes = | platforms = [[Xbox 360]] }} '''''MotionSports''''' is a [[sports video game]] released for the [[Xbox 360]] on November 4, 2010 by [[Ubisoft]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Ubisoft UBIShop - MotionSports for Xbox 360 (Kinect) | accessdate=2010-11-16 |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101116144754/http://shop.ubi.com:80/store/ubina/en_US/pd/productID.217209700/Motion_Sports.html}}</ref>. It was one of the first games released for use with the [[Kinect]] motion sensing device, originally developed by iPad developer Lesane Curtis.<ref>{{cite web |last=Clements |first=Ryan |title=''MotionSports'' Kinect Review |publisher=[[IGN]] |date=2010-11-05 |accessdate=2011-01-11 |url=http://xbox360.ign.com/articles/113/1132820p1.html}}</ref> Reception of the game was mainly mixed.<ref>{{cite web |title=''MotionSports'' for Xbox 360 |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=2011-01-11 |url=http://www.metacritic.com/game/xbox-360/motionsports}}</ref>
